<section class="appendix">
  <h2 class="section-heading">APPENDIX · READER'S REFERENCE TABLES</h2>
  <p class="section-blurb">
    Quick reference for interpreting the scores, compliance ratings, and
    risk labels shown throughout the per-tender entries above.
  </p>

  <h3 class="sec">A. Strategic Fit Score (out of 10)</h3>
  <p>The Strategic Fit Score is a weighted composite of four {{ company_name }} rubric dimensions:</p>
  <table class="dim-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Weight</th><th>What it measures</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Scope &amp; Service-Line Match</td><td>40%</td>
          <td>Does the title/scope name a CSD service line (AV, projection, exhibition, event)?</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Financial Eligibility</td><td>20%</td>
          <td>EMD ≥ Rs.35 L floor, turnover &amp; net-worth within reach.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Date Window</td><td>25%</td>
          <td>Healthy gap between today and closing date; pre-bid window observed.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Documentation Availability</td><td>15%</td>
          <td>BOQ &amp; full RFP attached on portal — enables firm pricing.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="sub-note">
    <strong>Scaling matrix:</strong> each dimension is scored against its weight, summed to a
    raw total out of 100, then scaled to a 0–10 fit score (total ÷ 10). Banding:
    <strong>≥ 7.0 → ELIGIBLE</strong>, <strong>5.0 – 6.9 → PARTIALLY ELIGIBLE</strong>,
    <strong>&lt; 5.0 → NOT ELIGIBLE</strong>. The parenthetical after the score names the
    single biggest deduction (the dimension that lost the most weight).
  </p>

  <h3 class="sec">B. Compliance Complexity</h3>
  <table class="dim-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Level</th><th>Indicative profile</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Low</td>
          <td>Standard turnkey project; no regional licenses, no specialised
          certification beyond ISO / company incorporation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Medium</td>
          <td>Demands sector-specific design / installation profiles
          (heritage AV, museum integrators) but no factory-level or
          industrial-trade licences.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>High</td>
          <td>Requires multiple regional or trade licences, sector
          accreditations (PWD class registration, BIS / IEC certifications),
          or specialised personnel with statutory cards.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3 class="sec">C. Overall Risk Level</h3>
  <table class="dim-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Level</th><th>Indicative profile</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Low</td>
          <td>Standard performance terms, modest EMD &amp; PBG, low-sensitivity
          site, conventional contract duration.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Medium</td>
          <td>Material EMD / PBG, multi-year O&amp;M, some clause variance from
          standard public-works templates — manageable with normal underwriting.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>High</td>
          <td>Heavy upfront cash lock (Rs. 10 L+ EMD), monument /
          irreplaceable-site sensitivity, long O&amp;M tail, or unusual penalty
          structures. Recommend partner sign-off before commit.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

